cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.LG. 

The paper is about implementing two probabilistic models, BM25 and BM25F, using the Lucene Java Framework for information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also mentions the use of plain text documents and documents with structure, which suggests that it could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the use of probabilistic models and the Lucene framework could also make it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
